1st February of 2017

I feel like I'm turning my Instagram into a Travel Diary.

Januari 2017 jadi bulan pertama dimana I missed two important celebrations with my family. 
Kangen Indonesia apalagi makanannya, jokesnya, curhatannya, dan kebersamaannya.
Pas CNY, liatin instagram, snapchat, dan facebook, semua isinya family group photo atau snap ngumpul-ngumpul.
Meanwhile I'm still trying my best to adapt here. But really, I wanna let you know, I love it here. I'd love to send you some postcards, simply dm me your complete address. 📮

I haven't met anyone who rejected me when I try to ask something (especially when i got lost). Some would even offer some helps.  But, you need to be able to be very independent. For instance, in a supermarket, you should be able to be your own cashier and you should swap your own card, you arrange your own timetable (the school cut down the courses to the essentials), when in doubt you should have courage to ask (you'll definitely regret it if you don't) 
And unlike people in Asian countries, people here tend to be more direct in speaking up their mind. They are used to it, so always remember to ask and explain, don't expect them to understand.

caption.text:
Travel Photos Alert ❕

Stiff as usual. 
After 9 days living here, there are too much stories to telI. Grateful to have been experiencing the culture, the facility, and the technology. I also found out many new interesting stuffs in Birmingham (glad to be new). Yet, I even started to see the same people around the city centre. (because the city isn't that big). However, I've discovered not only the good parts of it. I do think it's not that safe to be walking alone after 10.30 PM. (A stranger followed and asked me creepy questions once alrd). And the cold is definitely torturing, it has successfully made me eat more and buy more outside snacks/drinks in order to be able to feel warmer. But all in all, I'm happy that I've realized every small step that I take always leads me to some little miracles which I believe are God's gracious gifts.

I didn't mean you need to be in UK to be  happy, nevertheless, I encourage you to travel more, not only for sophistication, but to know more. #serendipity

caption.text:
Genuinely happy smiles? //
A Trip Review / Travel Experiences of
Gili Labak I

Jam 1.30 pagi berangkat ke Madura, lewat jembatan Suramadu, bisa liat pemandangan bulan purnama reflected on air persawahan. Setelah 3jam lebih, sampe dan tour guidenya jemput, tapi akhirnya di gabung sama kelompok lain naik kapal kayu yang cukup kecil tanpa tempat duduk yang nyaman. Awalnya airnya tenang ga ada sedikitpun ombak. Tapi di tengah perjalanan ternyata arah kita lawan arus ombak. Dan emang kita kurang persiapan dan ga ngerti apapun tentang kapal. Sesekali pas ombaknya tinggi, airnya masuk ke bagian depan kapan dan kita yang duduk (bawa kamera, tas kain, dll) di depan basah sama air laut. Conclusion?

Don't sit infront of the boat.

Cheers for those memories. // @ardeliaanisa muka si boss travel-planning kepotong. Thanks ya li for your hard work💪🏼 I thanked God for
• giving me the chance to travel with them
• giving me the chance to get to know them better
• the chance to learn from them
• the good laughs and the smiles
• the stories
• the games
• the experiences - Malang, Madura, Surabaya "Seize every moment, live everyday like it's your last." I keep reminding myself this sentence this week.  And it reminds me to always be grateful although things don't always turn out how you'd expected.
